rs Curriculum Requirements for Graduation General Education Requirements EN101  with a minimum grade of C  EN102  with a minimum grade of C  HI103  HI104  CH131  CH111  lab  CH132  CH112  lab  SE300  MA118  MA121 Liberal Arts Requirements 2 EN FA electives  2 HI electives  1 PO elective  1 PH PS elective Demonstrated competency if a foreign language equivalent to an Intermediate II level VMI Requirements PE101  PE102  PE200  PE201  PE211  3 PE Electives  not including PE 330  R O T C   including R O T C  or LS labs  for eight semester 2 writing intensive classes  at least one of which must be within the Economics and Business Department  Economics and Business Core Classes EC201  EC202  EC203  EC300  EC304  EC330  BU210  BU220  BU230  BU310  BU440  ALL EC BU Core courses must be taken at VMI  Economics and Business Electives 4 Economics Electives  EC405 for those cadets electing the Financial Management Concentration  FMC  4 Business electives  BU314  BU411  BU415  and either BU305  BU412 for those Cadets electing the Financial Management Concentration  Recommended Sequence First Semester  First Year   RATS EN101  HI103  CH131  CH111  MA118  PE101 2  ROTC  Foreign Language 101 Second Semester  First Year   RATS EN102  HI104  CH132  CH112  MA121  PE101 2  ROTC  Foreign Language 102 First Semester  Second Year    Third Class Year EC201  BU210  BU220  Liberal Arts Elective  PE 200 11  ROTC  Foreign Language 201  Second Semester  Second  Year   Third Class Year EC202  EC203  BU230  Liberal Arts Elective  FMC take BU 314  PE 200 11  ROTC  Foreign Language 202  SE 300 First Semester  Third Year   Second Class Year EC300  EC304  3 Liberal Arts Electives  PE201  ROTC Second Semester  Third  Year   Second Class Year EC330  BU310  Liberal Arts Elective  BU Elective  FMC take Liberal Arts Elective  PE Elective  ROTC First Semester  Fourth Year   First Class Year   FMC   see note below under I  2 EC Electives  2 BU Electives  1 Free Elective  PE Elective  ROTC Second Semester  Fourth  Year   First Class Year BU440  2 EC Electives  1 BU Elective  1 Free Elective  PE Elective  ROTC For FMC only  Due to scheduling constraints  cadets electing FMC may 3 EC electives in the first semester and two BU electives in the second semester  Any cadet who wishes to take a course away from the Institute MUST HAVE THE TRANSFER APPROVAL COMPLETED BEFORE taking the class  ALL EC BU Core courses must be taken at VMI    Check Off List First Semester  First Year   RATS     EN 101      HI 103      CH 131      CH 111      MA 118      PE 101 2      ROTC      Foreign Language 101 Second Semester  First Year   RATS     EN 102     HI 104     CH 132     CH 112     MA 121     PE 101 2     ROTC     Foreign Language 102   First Semester  Second Year   Third Class Year     EC 201     BU 210     BU 220     Liberal Arts Elective     PE 200 11     ROTC     Foreign Language 201   Second Semester  Second  Year   Third Class Year     EC 202     EC 203     BU 230     Liberal Arts Elective  FMC take BU 314      PE 200 11     ROTC     Foreign Language 202  SE 300   First Semester  Third Year   Second Class Year     EC 300     EC 304     3 Liberal Arts Electives             PE 201     ROTC Second Semester  Third  Year   Second Class Year     EC 330     BU 310     Liberal Arts Elective     BU Elective  FMC take Liberal Arts Elective      PE Elective     ROTC   First Semester  Fourth Year   First Class Year   FMC   see note above I      2 EC Electives         2 BU Electives         Free Elective     PE Elective     ROTC   Second Semester  Fourth  Year   First Class Year     BU 440     2 EC Electives         BU Elective     Free Elective     PE Elective     ROTC Col  Francis Bush Home Courses Links For My Advisees VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu Virginia Military Institute   Graduation Requirements   Francis Bush  skip to content VMI VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI Menu About About Us Administrative Offices Institute Report News  Photos  Videos VMI Archives Museums VMI Museum System The VMI Museum New Market Battlefield Stonewall Jackson House For Visitors Directions   Map Employment Parents   Family Conferences Chessie Nature Trail Bookstore Resources MyVMI Directories Friendly URLs Post View Health and Safety Computing Academics Areas of Study Majors   Minors Arts   Humanities Engineering Information   Social Sciences Life Sciences Natural Sciences ROTC Enrichment Institute Honors Program International Programs Service Opportunities Summer Programs Institute Writing Program Research Support Cadet Counseling Career Services Disabilities Services Miller Academic Center Advising Math Resource Center The Writing Center Resources Registrar Financial Aid Canvas Login Dean s Office Career Services Bookstore Cadet Computing Admissions Corps Life Athletics Library   Archives Preston Library Library Home Find Books Departments Media Equipment Technical Services Visitor Information Archives Archives Home Online Exhibits VMI History FAQs Genealogy   Alumni Manuscripts Civil War   New Market Give Close Menu Information   Social Sciences Economics   Business Home Degrees   Programs Courses Economics Newsletter Departmental Activities Policies   Forms About ECBU Faculty Open House Presentation Senior Exit Survey Alumni  97    07 survey Donna Potter Executive Secretary P   540  464 7234 F   540  464 7005 Virginia Military Institute 345 Scott Shipp Hall Lexington  VA  24450 Contact ECBU Graduation Requirements GPA and Grade Requirements for Graduation  GPA of 2 00 in all courses taken at VMI GPA of 2 00 in all EC BU taken at VMI A minimum grade of C in EN 101  EN 102  MA 118  MA 121  EC 201  EC 202  EC 203  EC 300  EC 304  EC 330  BU 210  BU 220  BU 230  BU 310  BU440 Total hours equal 136 hours Curriculum Requirements for Graduation General Education Requirements EN101  with a minimum grade of C  EN102  with a minimum grade of C  HI103  HI104  CH131  CH111  lab  CH132  CH112  lab  SE300  MA118  MA121 Liberal Arts Requirements 2 EN FA electives  2 HI electives  1 PO elective  1 PH PS elective Demonstrated competency if a foreign language equivalent to an Intermediate II level VMI Requirements PE101  PE102  PE200  PE201  PE211  3 PE Electives  not including PE 330  R O T C   including R O T C  or LS labs  for eight semester 2 writing intensive classes  at least one of which must be within the Economics and Business Department  Economics and Business Core Classes EC201  EC202  EC203  EC300  EC304  EC330  BU210  BU220  BU230  BU310  BU440  ALL EC BU Core courses must be taken at VMI  Economics and Business Electives 4 Economics Electives  EC405 for those cadets electing the Financial Management Concentration  FMC  4 Business electives  BU314  BU411  BU415  and either BU305  BU412 for those Cadets electing the Financial Management Concentration  Recommended Sequence First Semester  First Year   RATS EN101  HI103  CH131  CH111  MA118  PE101 2  ROTC  Foreign Language 101 Second Semester  First Year   RATS EN102  HI104  CH132  CH112  MA121  PE101 2  ROTC  Foreign Language 102 First Semester  Second Year    Third Class Year EC201  BU210  BU220  Liberal Arts Elective  PE 200 11  ROTC  Foreign Language 201  Second Semester  Second  Year   Third Class Year EC202  EC203  BU230  Liberal Arts Elective  FMC take BU 314  PE 200 11  ROTC  Foreign Language 202  SE 300 First Semester  Third Year   Second Class Year EC300  EC304  3 Liberal Arts Electives  PE201  ROTC Second Semester  Third  Year   Second Class Year EC330  BU310  Liberal Arts Elective  BU Elective  FMC take Liberal Arts Elective  PE Elective  ROTC First Semester  Fourth Year   First Class Year   FMC   see note below under I  2 EC Electives  2 BU Electives  1 Free Elective  PE Elective  ROTC Second Semester  Fourth  Year   First Class Year BU440  2 EC Electives  1 BU Elective  1 Free Elective  PE Elective  ROTC For FMC only  Due to scheduling constraints  cadets electing FMC may 3 EC electives in the first semester and two BU electives in the second semester  Any cadet who wishes to take a course away from the Institute MUST HAVE THE TRANSFER APPROVAL COMPLETED BEFORE taking the class  ALL EC BU Core courses must be taken at VMI    Check Off List First Semester  First Year   RATS     EN 101      HI 103      CH 131      CH 111      MA 118      PE 101 2      ROTC      Foreign Language 101 Second Semester  First Year   RATS     EN 102     HI 104     CH 132     CH 112     MA 121     PE 101 2     ROTC     Foreign Language 102   First Semester  Second Year   Third Class Year     EC 201     BU 210     BU 220     Liberal Arts Elective     PE 200 11     ROTC     Foreign Language 201   Second Semester  Second  Year   Third Class Year     EC 202     EC 203     BU 230     Liberal Arts Elective  FMC take BU 314      PE 200 11     ROTC     Foreign Language 202  SE 300   First Semester  Third Year   Second Class Year     EC 300     EC 304     3 Liberal Arts Electives             PE 201     ROTC Second Semester  Third  Year   Second Class Year     EC 330     BU 310     Liberal Arts Elective     BU Elective  FMC take Liberal Arts Elective      PE Elective     ROTC   First Semester  Fourth Year   First Class Year   FMC   see note above I      2 EC Electives         2 BU Electives         Free Elective     PE Elective     ROTC   Second Semester  Fourth  Year   First Class Year     BU 440     2 EC Electives         BU Elective     Free Elective     PE Elective     RO